text: I do think someone could make a case that removal/answer/counters are more efficient than ever and more accessible price wise that some cards on the ban list may not need to be there anymore.
It would still be a polarizing stance, but I think the grounds for that stance are stronger than it would have been a few years ago
Then how about a comparative list for answers to your top 10 banned cards. Of course having answers isn’t a factor really for the RC. The “Dies to Doomblade” argument.
I think it would be fun to do that style of articles. I know we keep throwing that out but we never actually do it
SCG did that for a while and I really enjoyed it. They'd ask a question and 2 writers each wrote a paragraph or 2 on it like "this card should be banned" or most powerful deck stuffs.
But keep it brief so we don't ramble and sound like morons like GDC did when they tried whole articles on the stance
I would like to write for something like this.
Tinker is obviously more broken than Flash/Hulk, but how much more broken?
If you trust people to do fair things with Hulk, then why not trust them to do fair things with Tinker?
And why is Coalition Victory still banned? Because it's boring? Then Lab Man needs to go on the list.
These are inflammatory lines of questioning, but they don't really feel out of line.
Hulk does have a limit on what it can get vs Tinker. Tinker could get anything...even a boat.
Ok, this is about to sound crazy, but in this day, is Tinker actually more broken than Flash/Hulk?
Yes. Flash Hulk requires both of those cards. Tinker just needs an artifact.
You all know the answer to this so Tinker probably isn’t the best example.

You’d have to pair it with another color.
If you're playing flash Hulk you're also in blue

Far fewer dependencies.

You could even land, sol ring, lotus petal tinker, because if you're a tinker deck you probably run petal effects

That said I haven’t played against it so I can’t speak as well. I accidentally ran Tinker in my Sharuum deck when I first started playing EDH because I didn’t know about the ban list.
